<refsect1>

<title>Description</title>

<para>&MiKTeX; configurations settings are read from the file
<filename>miktex.ini</filename>.</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1>

<title>Syntax</title>

<para>The syntax follows the informal conventions of a traditional
<ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/INI_file">INI file</ulink>.</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1>

<title>Querying and Modifying</title>

<para>It is recommended that you use the &MiKTeXConfigurationUtility;
(see
<citerefentry><refentrytitle>initexmf</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry>)
to query and modify configuration settings.</para>

</refsect1>

